1
00:00:14,768 --> 00:00:16,818
Dear.
- Yes.

2
00:00:16,908 --> 00:00:17,861
Come here.

3
00:00:18,743 --> 00:00:19,847
What is this?

4
00:00:20,210 --> 00:00:23,689
A dress for you on
this festival of Eid.

5
00:00:26,809 --> 00:00:28,030
Gorgeous!

6
00:00:28,779 --> 00:00:31,639
You're looking like a newly wed.

7
00:00:31,729 --> 00:00:34,099
Stop it! Wear it for some
more time, mom.

8
00:00:34,398 --> 00:00:38,696
I couldn't see you wearing these
clothes at your wedding,

9
00:00:38,974 --> 00:00:40,523
because I wasn't there.

10
00:00:40,774 --> 00:00:42,147
Let me watch you now.

11
00:00:42,237 --> 00:00:43,766
I'll slap you.

12
00:00:43,856 --> 00:00:47,183
My nephew is absolutely correct.
Why are you scolding him?

13
00:00:47,441 --> 00:00:50,673
Greetings Mr Maruti! Come in.
- Greetings!

14
00:00:50,929 --> 00:00:53,170
You really look wonderful!

15
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:54,422
Keep it here.

16
00:00:54,512 --> 00:00:57,775
Even your wife is beautiful.
- That's what I'm saying.

17
00:00:58,465 --> 00:01:02,649
Look at my kid.
He looks like his mother.

18
00:01:02,739 --> 00:01:04,509
What are you saying?
- Quiet!

19
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:09,266
God has tattooed
my complexion on his sole.

20
00:01:09,507 --> 00:01:12,919
If he would've taken my
complexion even by mistake,

21
00:01:13,009 --> 00:01:16,152
we had to mark twice for
removing to prevent bad luck!

22
00:01:16,242 --> 00:01:18,679
A black mark is very auspicious.

23
00:01:18,976 --> 00:01:22,898
Auspicious? His soles have wheels.
He moves so quickly!

24
00:01:25,492 --> 00:01:27,392
I'll always cherish this day.

25
00:01:27,482 --> 00:01:29,942
No one would forget
such an auspicious day.

26
00:01:30,032 --> 00:01:31,690
Maruti, are you in Mumbai now?

27
00:01:31,938 --> 00:01:34,418
I have a good hold over Mumbai.

28
00:01:34,508 --> 00:01:37,111
The train won't move
until I reach the station.

29
00:01:37,424 --> 00:01:38,654
Give brother too.

30
00:01:38,929 --> 00:01:40,256
Have it brother.

31
00:01:42,289 --> 00:01:43,467
It's time to leave for duty.

32
00:01:43,931 --> 00:01:46,921
I'll go with you too.
- Yes! Quickly eat!

33
00:01:47,362 --> 00:01:48,919
Wrap him tight.

34
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:51,799
You promised to take me.
- I'll take you!

35
00:01:51,889 --> 00:01:55,159
We'll leave to catch our train.
- So early?

36
00:01:55,249 --> 00:01:57,797
I'll drop her at Kolhapur
and leave for Mumbai.

37
00:01:57,887 --> 00:01:59,649
Come along, brother, I'll drop you
at the bus stop. - Let's go.

38
00:01:59,739 --> 00:02:00,830
Bye, dear.
- Bye.

39
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,706
Come son.

40
00:02:01,796 --> 00:02:03,995
Good bye sister!
- Okay.

41
00:02:07,492 --> 00:02:08,946
'CENTRAL JAIL'

42
00:02:12,669 --> 00:02:13,770
Welcome sir.

43
00:02:14,109 --> 00:02:16,290
Congratulations on your
release after 10 long years.

44
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:19,159
Just one garland?

45
00:02:19,636 --> 00:02:21,249
Where's the second one?
- Second?

46
00:02:21,631 --> 00:02:24,631
The other garland that I was
supposed to offer Salma?

47
00:02:26,545 --> 00:02:28,855
Why are you quiet?

48
00:02:28,945 --> 00:02:30,057
It's too late.

49
00:02:30,147 --> 00:02:31,809
Salma..
- What happened?

50
00:02:32,169 --> 00:02:34,675
Salma got married
after you were jailed.

51
00:02:34,765 --> 00:02:35,747
No!

52
00:02:36,722 --> 00:02:38,379
She can't get married
to someone else.

53
00:02:39,123 --> 00:02:44,109
It would be my defeat and
I've never learnt to accept defeat.

54
00:02:48,015 --> 00:02:50,385
Recognize me?
- Zafar?

55
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:54,307
Did you think I would
never return from jail?

56
00:02:54,696 --> 00:02:57,014
That you got your daughter
married to someone else.

57
00:02:57,501 --> 00:02:59,883
We learnt your true colours.

58
00:02:59,973 --> 00:03:03,786
You're a murderer!
You've cheated people of millions!

59
00:03:03,876 --> 00:03:08,466
I did all that for your daughter.

60
00:03:08,849 --> 00:03:11,409
And you got her married
to a beggar!

61
00:03:11,928 --> 00:03:14,909
Listen! You still have a chance.

62
00:03:15,223 --> 00:03:17,592
Get her divorced
and married to me.

63
00:03:17,905 --> 00:03:18,874
Divorce?

64
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:21,003
Impossible!

65
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:25,323
I prefer my daughter to die,

66
00:03:25,413 --> 00:03:30,658
rather than getting her married
to a devil like you.

67
00:03:30,856 --> 00:03:36,773
I'll kill your son-in-law and
forcefully take Salma away.

68
00:03:36,863 --> 00:03:40,133
No, I won't let that happen.

69
00:03:40,515 --> 00:03:42,598
Move!
- Zafar!

70
00:03:43,328 --> 00:03:46,443
Zafar, it's a crime!

71
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,363
At least fear god.

72
00:03:48,735 --> 00:03:51,862
I am god,
I'm not scared of any other god.

73
00:04:17,655 --> 00:04:18,767
Let's go, Goga.

74
00:04:29,073 --> 00:04:30,322
Allah Rakha...

75
00:04:36,564 --> 00:04:41,646
You have stayed with us for years.
You must look after my family.

76
00:04:42,426 --> 00:04:44,095
It is your responsibility.

77
00:04:44,751 --> 00:04:48,745
Deliver this message to Salma.

78
00:04:49,635 --> 00:04:51,520
Fly away!

79
00:05:10,190 --> 00:05:11,186
You?

80
00:05:14,969 --> 00:05:16,052
Why are you here?

81
00:05:16,623 --> 00:05:21,253
To take Salma
whom I was to marry 10 years ago.

82
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:25,491
Have some shame.
I'm a married woman.

83
00:05:25,904 --> 00:05:28,416
I don't follow
the rules of society.

84
00:05:29,011 --> 00:05:32,678
The world knows
I acquire what I want.

85
00:05:33,219 --> 00:05:35,781
I'm stubborn by birth.

86
00:05:38,943 --> 00:05:40,971
How many doors will you close?

87
00:05:41,637 --> 00:05:44,434
I'll break open
all the doors of the world.

88
00:05:44,787 --> 00:05:46,882
Be afraid of God and His wrath.

89
00:05:47,134 --> 00:05:49,678
Neither do I believe in God,
nor His wrath.

90
00:05:50,386 --> 00:05:53,094
I'm a disaster for the one
who doesn't listen to me.

91
00:06:02,626 --> 00:06:07,087
Wait, Zafar!
I'll make this fire a pyre for you.

92
00:06:07,177 --> 00:06:08,219
Don't be a fool.

93
00:06:08,506 --> 00:06:10,594
Look at his hut.

94
00:06:10,844 --> 00:06:14,046
I'll keep you in a palace
and bathe you in gems.

95
00:06:14,136 --> 00:06:16,094
For an Indian woman like me,

96
00:06:16,428 --> 00:06:19,136
a husband's house is a palace,

97
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:24,980
this scarf she wears
is as good as silk

98
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:31,052
and the dust of my husband's feet
is more than your gems.

99
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,678
Really?

100
00:06:33,194 --> 00:06:35,136
What if I kill your husband?

101
00:06:35,511 --> 00:06:37,720
There'll be
two dead bodies lying here,

102
00:06:38,069 --> 00:06:40,052
one, my husband's and mine.

103
00:06:40,344 --> 00:06:44,177
Get out or I'll call
the entire neighbourhood.

104
00:06:44,348 --> 00:06:47,553
They'll drive you out
after a good thrashing.

105
00:06:49,177 --> 00:06:50,177
Good.

106
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:53,136
I'm leaving this place right now,

107
00:06:53,721 --> 00:06:56,636
but I'll leave this city
only with my Salma.

108
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:09,469
What's the matter, Allahrakha?

109
00:07:45,408 --> 00:07:46,400
He's the one.

110
00:08:18,136 --> 00:08:19,749
Dad!

111
00:08:22,494 --> 00:08:24,261
Dad!

112
00:08:26,609 --> 00:08:29,805
Dad! Let me go.

113
00:08:30,189 --> 00:08:31,848
Dad!

114
00:09:22,808 --> 00:09:23,764
Oh, lord!

115
00:09:24,387 --> 00:09:26,122
Mom!

116
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:45,977
Goga!

117
00:09:53,396 --> 00:09:55,557
Mother!

118
00:09:59,490 --> 00:10:01,349
Take us too!

119
00:10:01,439 --> 00:10:02,696
Get lost!

120
00:10:49,355 --> 00:10:51,306
Apply a black mark on him
once you reach Kolhapur.

121
00:10:51,396 --> 00:10:53,063
Stop!

122
00:10:55,168 --> 00:10:56,270
Why did you stop the cart?

123
00:10:56,896 --> 00:10:59,556
Can't you see the water ahead?

124
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,640
It's risky to proceed.

125
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:03,344
He's correct, let's not go.

126
00:11:03,434 --> 00:11:06,142
Don't get scared by his warnings.
- You don't worry.

127
00:11:06,232 --> 00:11:11,098
We'll miss the bus.
Take Rs. 20 and let's go.

128
00:11:11,188 --> 00:11:14,689
Come on! Move!
- They only want money.

129
00:11:15,272 --> 00:11:19,049
No, please listen to me.

130
00:11:28,895 --> 00:11:31,407
My son! Save my son.

131
00:11:31,497 --> 00:11:34,145
Parvati!
- Save my son.

132
00:11:35,251 --> 00:11:36,938
My son!

133
00:11:39,411 --> 00:11:41,406
Parvati!
- Help!

134
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:48,489
Parvati!

135
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:51,261
My son! Help!

136
00:11:51,467 --> 00:11:53,051
Parvati!

137
00:11:53,424 --> 00:11:57,347
No! My son!

138
00:11:58,263 --> 00:12:01,345
My, son! Please someone
save my son.

139
00:12:01,667 --> 00:12:03,390
Parvati!

140
00:12:21,487 --> 00:12:23,305
I'm an orphan now.

141
00:12:23,395 --> 00:12:25,719
I have no one now!

142
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:39,015
God, despite your presence,
you made me an orphan.

143
00:12:41,810 --> 00:12:43,107
Uncle!

144
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:48,125
You lost everything,
so did I.

145
00:12:49,345 --> 00:12:53,633
We have to support each other.
Let's go.

146
00:12:53,797 --> 00:12:56,811
The accident
has left her traumatised.

147
00:12:57,075 --> 00:12:58,398
She has lost her speech.

148
00:12:58,542 --> 00:13:00,145
Can she never speak?

149
00:13:00,494 --> 00:13:02,603
Did she have a child?
- Yes, but...

150
00:13:02,693 --> 00:13:05,750
Get him. We can't treat her
unless he's here.

151
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:08,651
How can we find her child?
- I'm sorry.

152
00:13:08,809 --> 00:13:11,379
It's necessary to get her child.

153
00:13:11,469 --> 00:13:12,321
Doctor!
- Coming!

154
00:13:12,411 --> 00:13:13,553
But doctor...

155
00:13:14,136 --> 00:13:15,512
Why are you worried?

156
00:13:16,220 --> 00:13:18,121
We'll get a kid somehow.

157
00:13:19,711 --> 00:13:22,088
Today's breaking news!

158
00:13:22,178 --> 00:13:25,345
America created a hydrogen bomb!
Aeroplanes are on a 7-day strike.

159
00:13:25,512 --> 00:13:27,806
Today's breaking news!

160
00:13:28,661 --> 00:13:29,804
Uncle Rahim!

161
00:13:29,969 --> 00:13:31,361
It's a one-day journey...

162
00:13:31,637 --> 00:13:32,762
When you reach...
- Hello, Uncle Rahim.

163
00:13:32,886 --> 00:13:34,414
Greetings, son.

164
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,480
Are you going to Ajmer Sharif?
- No.

165
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:43,609
Today's breaking news. America...
- Hey, paper boy.

166
00:13:43,762 --> 00:13:44,720
Today's...

167
00:13:45,261 --> 00:13:48,829
Are you going to Ajmer Sharif?
- No!

168
00:13:50,554 --> 00:13:54,326
Sir, be seated.
I'll be back with the change. - Okay.

169
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:59,921
Bob, I've established
a chit fund office

170
00:14:00,011 --> 00:14:01,879
for you in Mumbai too.
- Okay.

171
00:14:01,969 --> 00:14:05,558
But make sure my name
doesn't appear in these matters.

172
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:06,762
Understand?

173
00:14:08,438 --> 00:14:09,536
Come.

174
00:14:12,489 --> 00:14:13,487
Sir.

175
00:14:15,512 --> 00:14:16,553
Sir.

176
00:14:20,499 --> 00:14:23,208
Madam, are you going to Ajmer?

177
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:28,914
Will you offer a sacred sheet
at the shrine?

178
00:14:29,628 --> 00:14:32,172
Pray that I get my mom back.

179
00:14:34,085 --> 00:14:35,178
Mother!

180
00:14:36,304 --> 00:14:39,879
Mom, where were you?

181
00:14:39,969 --> 00:14:41,046
This is my mom!

182
00:14:41,136 --> 00:14:42,795
I'm her son, Iqbal!
- Get out!

183
00:14:42,885 --> 00:14:46,932
Get out!
- Let go of me! Mother!

184
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:49,545
Nurse, bring the child.
- Yes, sir.

185
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:55,053
Madam, this is your son.

186
00:14:55,637 --> 00:14:56,753
Get out!

187
00:14:57,804 --> 00:14:58,755
What happened?

188
00:14:58,845 --> 00:15:00,637
Thank God,
Salma lost her memory,

189
00:15:01,136 --> 00:15:02,885
or this boy
would've taken her away.

190
00:15:03,143 --> 00:15:04,804
Do I kill him?
- Kill him.

191
00:15:06,053 --> 00:15:06,921
Mom!

192
00:15:07,011 --> 00:15:09,386
Come on, silly kid!

193
00:15:09,512 --> 00:15:10,969
Stand still.

194
00:15:12,428 --> 00:15:14,608
Bob!
- Let go! Mother!

195
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,553
Mom!

196
00:15:18,785 --> 00:15:20,637
Leave me!

197
00:15:20,975 --> 00:15:22,063
Mom!

198
00:15:22,804 --> 00:15:26,755
Don't go away, mom,
I'm your son, Iqbal.

199
00:15:26,845 --> 00:15:29,795
Don't leave me!

200
00:15:29,885 --> 00:15:31,588
For God's sake,
don't leave me!

201
00:15:31,678 --> 00:15:34,921
I'm your son!
Stop, mother!

202
00:15:35,011 --> 00:15:38,755
For God's sake, don't leave me!
Stop, mother!

203
00:15:38,845 --> 00:15:40,755
Don't leave!

204
00:15:40,845 --> 00:15:42,423
I'm your son.

205
00:15:45,053 --> 00:15:47,595
Why don't you speak, mom?

206
00:15:50,553 --> 00:15:53,011
Don't leave me!

207
00:16:07,178 --> 00:16:08,885
Mother!

208
00:16:10,512 --> 00:16:12,594
Leave me!

209
00:16:22,462 --> 00:16:24,068
Uncle!

210
00:16:25,502 --> 00:16:27,668
You scoundrel!

211
00:16:42,421 --> 00:16:43,545
Uncle!

212
00:17:01,247 --> 00:17:02,466
Scoundrel!

213
00:17:27,778 --> 00:17:30,676
Don't worry, uncle,
I'm your right hand from today.

214
00:17:31,134 --> 00:17:33,212
We'll share all our troubles!

215
00:17:36,824 --> 00:17:41,753
Allah Rakha, both of us will
take care of porters from now on.

216
00:17:47,736 --> 00:17:49,834
'415 Express train...'

217
00:17:50,034 --> 00:17:55,027
'arriving by...'

218
00:18:04,116 --> 00:18:05,155
'INDIAN RAILWAYS'

219
00:18:14,138 --> 00:18:15,188
Porter!

220
00:18:18,812 --> 00:18:20,034
Come.

221
00:18:24,545 --> 00:18:25,970
'Brother!'

222
00:18:29,392 --> 00:18:30,586
Hurry up!

223
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:31,957
Quickly!

224
00:18:36,923 --> 00:18:38,215
You dropped the dog!

225
00:18:39,713 --> 00:18:42,406
You scoundrel! You dropped
my dog.

226
00:18:42,496 --> 00:18:43,644
Bloody fool!

227
00:18:49,139 --> 00:18:52,346
Sir, why are you beating a porter?

228
00:18:54,274 --> 00:18:55,430
What's the matter, uncle?

229
00:18:56,871 --> 00:18:58,758
Hey, he is bleeding!

230
00:19:02,203 --> 00:19:07,042
Sir, you can't
beat them up like this.

231
00:19:07,132 --> 00:19:10,542
You dog! How dare you touch me!

232
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,625
Don't move!

233
00:19:14,715 --> 00:19:20,042
I'll suspend you! I'm a member
of the railway advisory board.

234
00:19:20,251 --> 00:19:22,845
You thrashed our colleague
and we...

235
00:19:22,935 --> 00:19:26,667
Don't you dare move
or else I'll shoot.

236
00:19:27,242 --> 00:19:29,375
What can you do?

237
00:19:44,215 --> 00:19:45,272
What's the matter, Allahrakha?

238
00:19:49,664 --> 00:19:50,619
Really?

239
00:19:51,588 --> 00:19:52,750
Let's see.

240
00:20:26,424 --> 00:20:27,696
Who are you?

241
00:20:31,428 --> 00:20:34,326
Open the window for a while.

242
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,251
My introduction is very lengthy.

243
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,125
I've the blessings of God
right from childhood,

244
00:20:39,997 --> 00:20:41,667
and I've got Allahrakha with me.

245
00:20:42,375 --> 00:20:46,618
I've got badge no. 786,
I smoke cigar no. 20, I'm a porter

246
00:20:46,708 --> 00:20:48,482
and my name is...
- Iqbal!

247
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:51,942
The one whom I hit on the head,
becomes bald.

248
00:20:52,032 --> 00:20:53,084
What do you want?

249
00:20:54,290 --> 00:20:57,750
A worker should get his wages
before his sweat dries.

250
00:20:58,021 --> 00:21:01,209
But he got a thrashing.

251
00:21:01,763 --> 00:21:04,332
It's better
that you apologize to him.

252
00:21:04,422 --> 00:21:05,332
Never.

253
00:21:06,817 --> 00:21:07,750
No?

254
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:11,667
Think about it.

255
00:21:13,153 --> 00:21:16,375
If a porter, who lifts others'
burdens becomes a burden on you,

256
00:21:17,095 --> 00:21:18,583
you'll have a tough time.

257
00:21:19,489 --> 00:21:22,251
Seems you'll leave
only after a good fight.

258
00:21:22,501 --> 00:21:24,251
Where will I go?

259
00:21:24,919 --> 00:21:28,009
The railway platform is our home.
What say, brothers? - Yes!

260
00:21:28,099 --> 00:21:29,708
These are the guests.
- Yes.

261
00:21:29,969 --> 00:21:32,058
So house owners will...
- Stay back!

262
00:21:32,292 --> 00:21:34,105
And guests...
- Will leave!

263
00:21:34,195 --> 00:21:36,209
What say, brother?

264
00:21:37,363 --> 00:21:38,995
Would you like to try?

265
00:21:39,998 --> 00:21:42,625
Allarakha, watch the fun.
- Come.

266
