- What misbehaviour is this?

782
01:06:05,250 --> 01:06:07,081
Drive them out!
Michael!

783
01:06:07,416 --> 01:06:08,733
You want Michael?

784
01:06:09,416 --> 01:06:11,749
There's Michael and party.

785
01:06:12,124 --> 01:06:14,917
Excuse me.
They're your guests.

786
01:06:15,007 --> 01:06:17,285
You invite them
and then drive them out?

787
01:06:17,375 --> 01:06:18,624
This isn't good.

788
01:06:18,958 --> 01:06:21,026
Bad publicity.

789
01:06:22,208 --> 01:06:24,833
Vicky, call the other people
and ask why they aren't here.

790
01:06:26,658 --> 01:06:28,749
One pose please.
- Of course.

791
01:06:28,916 --> 01:06:30,770
Put your arm around him.
- Why not?

792
01:06:33,583 --> 01:06:34,624
Smile please.

793
01:06:42,291 --> 01:06:44,542
Hello.
- Hello, Uncle Zafar, I'm Vicky.

794
01:06:44,839 --> 01:06:49,375
Vicky, I have an invitation
to your engagement.

795
01:06:49,500 --> 01:06:50,835
What happened?
- What?

796
01:06:50,999 --> 01:06:52,749
Today is the 2nd, my engagement.

797
01:06:53,022 --> 01:06:54,707
Today?
- Today's the 2nd.

798
01:06:54,896 --> 01:06:55,874
'Engagement ceremony
of Shri Vicky with Julie.'

799
01:06:55,964 --> 01:06:58,958
The date printed is the 20th.
- How did it change?

800
01:06:59,333 --> 01:07:01,521
Like 5 changes to 50.

801
01:07:03,231 --> 01:07:06,707
You taught this to us
and we used it on you.

802
01:07:07,458 --> 01:07:10,833
So, you did this?
- Yes.

803
01:07:13,837 --> 01:07:14,797
Thank you.

804
01:07:14,941 --> 01:07:17,999
We did this, thanks to you.

805
01:07:18,500 --> 01:07:23,707
Till you don't give us houses,
we'll stay in your house.

806
01:07:25,205 --> 01:07:26,213
We'll consider it our own.

807
01:07:26,303 --> 01:07:27,879
What do you say?
- Yes!

808
01:07:28,041 --> 01:07:30,999
Excuse me, could you
throw some light on this?

809
01:07:31,416 --> 01:07:33,583
Is this your way to get the houses?

810
01:07:33,934 --> 01:07:34,916
Sir,

811
01:07:35,431 --> 01:07:39,041
you took our money in your way,
we'll get the houses, our way.

812
01:07:39,361 --> 01:07:42,083
You want houses, right?
- Yes.

813
01:07:42,223 --> 01:07:43,293
You'll get them.

814
01:07:48,468 --> 01:07:49,583
Excuse me!

815
01:07:50,353 --> 01:07:54,041
They have a right to the houses
and you've grown pale.

816
01:07:54,751 --> 01:07:55,999
Do you want to say something?

817
01:07:57,250 --> 01:08:02,624
They'll get the houses
that they have a right on. - I see.

818
01:08:18,731 --> 01:08:19,932
You want a house, right?

819
01:08:21,090 --> 01:08:22,224
Here.

820
01:08:23,166 --> 01:08:24,307
Happy?

821
01:08:26,022 --> 01:08:29,141
What happened?
Are they small?

822
01:08:32,749 --> 01:08:35,099
It's bigger than your heart.

823
01:08:36,825 --> 01:08:38,455
We'll provide what's necessary

824
01:08:39,763 --> 01:08:44,587
for rich people like
you in this house.

825
01:08:49,391 --> 01:08:50,932
Move away!

826
01:08:52,575 --> 01:08:53,766
What are you doing?

827
01:08:54,363 --> 01:08:56,890
I'm trying to decrease the size
of this chandelier,

828
01:08:57,558 --> 01:09:00,766
or it won't fit in this house.

829
01:09:00,966 --> 01:09:02,474
Iqbal.
- Yes!

830
01:09:02,564 --> 01:09:06,210
Could you throw some light
on the chandeliers and the houses?

831
01:09:06,391 --> 01:09:09,031
I'm about to throw many things.

832
01:09:09,572 --> 01:09:10,717
Wait and watch.

833
01:09:10,932 --> 01:09:13,391
Do you know how costly that was?
- Excuse me!

834
01:09:13,779 --> 01:09:16,635
What do you think about the
chandelier in pieces? - Shut up!

835
01:09:16,725 --> 01:09:17,502
I will.

836
01:09:17,641 --> 01:09:19,447
Iqbal...
- What?

837
01:09:19,641 --> 01:09:21,684
I use a plate as a mirror.

838
01:09:21,890 --> 01:09:23,994
You want a mirror?
You'll get it.

839
01:09:32,605 --> 01:09:34,224
I would've photographed it,
had I known.

840
01:09:34,582 --> 01:09:36,766
Binbal?
- Yes, Iqbal.

841
01:09:37,391 --> 01:09:41,474
Can you see yourself?
- Yes. It's great.

842
01:09:41,613 --> 01:09:42,766
Excuse me!

843
01:09:43,182 --> 01:09:46,059
It's unlucky for a mirror
to break during an engagement.

844
01:09:46,149 --> 01:09:48,057
What do you think about it?

845
01:09:49,849 --> 01:09:54,344
A clock is necessary
for us to reach on time. - Yes!

846
01:09:54,516 --> 01:09:57,294
Just a moment!
Smile!

847
01:09:58,608 --> 01:10:00,425
Now break it.
- There we go!

848
01:10:03,683 --> 01:10:05,321
Uncle!
- Yes!

849
01:10:05,411 --> 01:10:10,141
Friends, take your share.

850
01:10:10,266 --> 01:10:14,641
Your misbehaviour...
- This pendulum moves,

851
01:10:14,932 --> 01:10:19,599
it keeps moving.
This time belongs to us now. - I...

852
01:10:19,921 --> 01:10:22,951
What's your opinion
about this moving pendulum?

853
01:10:23,041 --> 01:10:24,103
Shut up!

854
01:10:24,193 --> 01:10:25,849
Vicky, call the police!

855
01:10:27,673 --> 01:10:28,849
Wait a minute!

856
01:10:30,355 --> 01:10:31,349
Now break it!

857
01:10:33,931 --> 01:10:34,932
Hello!

858
01:10:37,141 --> 01:10:40,433
I want a fan.
- I want it.

859
01:10:44,659 --> 01:10:45,849
Hold it!

860
01:10:47,307 --> 01:10:49,063
Thank you. Your turn.

861
01:10:49,910 --> 01:10:51,278
'Yeah, so what was I saying?'

862
01:10:57,312 --> 01:10:59,184
What's all this?

863
01:10:59,391 --> 01:11:00,849
Who are these people?

864
01:11:02,391 --> 01:11:04,890
So you've reached here too.

865
01:11:04,980 --> 01:11:07,806
We're guests.
We received the invitation cards.

866
01:11:07,932 --> 01:11:11,141
Uncle Ramu, did you get everything
or is there anything left?

867
01:11:11,266 --> 01:11:13,222
He only wants a wife now.

868
01:11:13,312 --> 01:11:14,683
A wife?

869
01:11:15,806 --> 01:11:17,474
A wife!
- Let go!

870
01:11:17,805 --> 01:11:18,759
Uncle.

871
01:11:18,849 --> 01:11:21,141
Look at yourself and me.

872
01:11:21,231 --> 01:11:22,641
Does this girl suit you?

873
01:11:23,711 --> 01:11:26,932
I'm keeping her for me.

874
01:11:27,022 --> 01:11:30,759
He's holding my hand
and you aren't doing anything.

875
01:11:30,849 --> 01:11:33,307
He's come with so many men.

876
01:11:33,849 --> 01:11:36,141
I would've dealt with him
if he was alone.

877
01:11:36,440 --> 01:11:38,755
Consider me alone.

878
01:11:40,998 --> 01:11:43,558
I need to settle
a few matters with you.

879
01:11:43,932 --> 01:11:45,849
Do I settle them now?
- Sure.

880
01:11:46,532 --> 01:11:47,683
Leave him.

881
01:12:43,024 --> 01:12:46,228
In a minute this iron
will pierce your chest!

882
01:12:46,384 --> 01:12:49,039
We are workers and
our chest is an iron wall!

883
01:12:49,503 --> 01:12:51,138
And these are our tools.

884
01:12:51,783 --> 01:12:55,473
They help us sustain our livelihood
and can destroy you as well.

885
01:14:02,080 --> 01:14:05,209
Hey, excuse me. Hello!

886
01:14:05,593 --> 01:14:07,581
Smile, smile smile.
- No!

887
01:14:11,969 --> 01:14:14,817
Your body is sinking
because of the eagle's weight.

888
01:14:14,907 --> 01:14:16,680
Do you have anything to say?

889
01:14:17,989 --> 01:14:20,736
Oh I forgot.
You can't speak.

890
01:14:20,826 --> 01:14:23,840
Cheers for Iqbal!

891
01:14:23,930 --> 01:14:25,256
What are you doing?
- C'mon!

892
01:14:25,346 --> 01:14:28,470
Just a moment Iqbal, smile!
- Leave me.

893
01:14:28,860 --> 01:14:31,846
Uncle, call the police.
- What are you doing?

894
01:14:32,013 --> 01:14:33,346
Uncle, call the police.

895
01:14:33,690 --> 01:14:37,478
She will stay with us
till we get our homes.

896
01:14:37,906 --> 01:14:40,898
Any comments? I'll be back
in a while. Let's go guys! -Uncle!

897
01:14:41,451 --> 01:14:42,848
Uncle! Uncle, call the police.

898
01:14:43,001 --> 01:14:47,435
So, these porters defeated
and embarrased you...

899
01:14:47,697 --> 01:14:49,107
What is your opinion on this?

900
01:14:49,623 --> 01:14:50,786
Shut up!

901
01:14:50,876 --> 01:14:52,533
You shut up!

902
01:14:56,705 --> 01:15:00,538
Leave me! I said leave me!
- Don't move your legs.

903
01:15:00,628 --> 01:15:03,903
Shut up and sit here.

904
01:15:04,081 --> 01:15:08,442
Sit! Lie down!

905
01:15:11,715 --> 01:15:15,893
I'm warning you, let me go!
I'll send you to jail.

906
01:15:15,983 --> 01:15:19,106
I'll handcuff you now.

907
01:15:19,196 --> 01:15:23,792
Next I'll send your partner
to jail.

908
01:15:23,882 --> 01:15:25,583
Leave me!
- Shut up!

909
01:15:26,499 --> 01:15:32,083
Or I'll break you like
I broke your house at the party.

910
01:15:33,131 --> 01:15:34,953
Big talks.

911
01:15:35,542 --> 01:15:37,375
Will you have food?
- No.

912
01:15:37,666 --> 01:15:40,127
Don't eat.
I'm telling you to sing.

913
01:15:49,363 --> 01:15:52,516
Water is leaking!

914
01:15:52,606 --> 01:15:58,554
Look ma'am, you get water through
taps, we get it from the roof.

915
01:15:59,360 --> 01:16:01,785
I can't cook here now.

916
01:16:01,875 --> 01:16:05,094
'Welcome to Akashvani Radio'

917
01:16:05,708 --> 01:16:09,042
'We present Swami Sevanand
on a special programme.'

918
01:16:09,132 --> 01:16:12,447
'We'll now teach you
various methods of doing yoga.'

919
01:16:13,092 --> 01:16:14,104
Oh, yes!

920
01:16:14,583 --> 01:16:18,750
Chef Khan was supposed to teach us
a new recipe with eggs.

921
01:16:19,042 --> 01:16:22,047
What time is it?
Yes!

922
01:16:23,708 --> 01:16:29,417
'Mr. Latif and Mr. Hanif will teach
you how to make a French omelette.'

923
01:16:29,824 --> 01:16:34,417
'Mr. Latif and Mr. Hanif...'
- This is why I'm strong!

924
01:16:34,708 --> 01:16:37,417
'Are you ready
to make an omelette?' - Yes.

925
01:16:37,507 --> 01:16:39,250
'Take clarified butter.'

926
01:16:41,454 --> 01:16:44,750
'Add one teaspoon
of clarified butter...' - Okay.

927
01:16:45,493 --> 01:16:48,042
'Add an onion.'
- An onion!

928
01:16:48,132 --> 01:16:52,582
'Keep all the spices ready.'

929
01:16:53,173 --> 01:16:56,392
'We'll assist you
on the further steps.'

930
01:16:57,172 --> 01:16:59,833
'Stand on one foot and jump.'

931
01:17:00,134 --> 01:17:02,542
'It's necessary for good health.'

932
01:17:05,198 --> 01:17:07,083
'Now stop.'

933
01:17:08,242 --> 01:17:10,631
'Do you have an egg?'
- Yes.

934
01:17:10,721 --> 01:17:14,159
'Sit on it in a yoga position,
on the ground.' - Yoga!

935
01:17:14,249 --> 01:17:16,958
'First sit down.'

936
01:17:17,915 --> 01:17:20,375
I'll sit.
- 'Sit cross-legged.'

937
01:17:22,007 --> 01:17:26,501
'Place your hands on your knees
and close your eyes.'

938
01:17:28,589 --> 01:17:31,661
'Fry it on a low flame.'

939
01:17:31,817 --> 01:17:34,356
'It's moving a lot.'

940
01:17:34,496 --> 01:17:36,243
'Yoga...'

941
01:17:38,231 --> 01:17:39,949
'Slowly...'

942
01:17:40,039 --> 01:17:42,295
'Listen carefully.'

943
01:17:42,385 --> 01:17:43,837
Where did this
chick come from?

944
01:17:44,359 --> 01:17:46,582
'Now take a green chilli.'

945
01:17:47,071 --> 01:17:48,057
Yes.

946
01:17:48,432 --> 01:17:50,833
'Open your mouth
and hang your tongue out.'

947
01:17:51,980 --> 01:17:54,755
'Add the chilli to it.'

948
01:17:55,048 --> 01:17:57,459
'It's necessary for a good taste.'

949
01:18:05,676 --> 01:18:06,679
Chilli!

950
01:18:07,477 --> 01:18:10,792
'Now lie down, slowly.'

951
01:18:10,882 --> 01:18:12,189
Lie down!

952
01:18:12,279 --> 01:18:15,167
'Lift your left leg.'
- Left leg!

953
01:18:15,459 --> 01:18:16,576
'Then the right leg.'
- Right!

954
01:18:16,666 --> 01:18:18,369
Both legs!
- 'With both legs...'

955
01:18:18,542 --> 01:18:19,542
'Get an onion.'

956
01:18:19,708 --> 01:18:21,993
Yes.
- 'Yes, an onion.'

957
01:18:22,083 --> 01:18:25,792
'Hanif will tell you
what has to be done next.'

958
01:18:26,313 --> 01:18:29,875
'Keep it on the ground
and punch it.'

959
01:18:31,625 --> 01:18:33,792
Break it!
- 'After that...'

960
01:18:34,395 --> 01:18:37,216
'Add it to the pan

961
01:18:37,306 --> 01:18:40,750
and wait till it turns red.'

962
01:18:41,131 --> 01:18:42,833
'Now stand up.'

963
01:18:44,833 --> 01:18:47,570
'Place your hands on your knees'
- What?

964
01:18:48,292 --> 01:18:52,167
'tuck your tummy in,
and inhale.'

965
01:18:54,446 --> 01:18:56,743
'Don't move.'

966
01:18:56,833 --> 01:19:00,361
'Moving isn't good
- 1 2...

967
01:19:00,451 --> 01:19:02,993
for the health.'

968
01:19:03,083 --> 01:19:04,913
'Take another egg.'

969
01:19:05,501 --> 01:19:08,417
'Break it and put it in the pan.'

970
01:19:09,000 --> 01:19:10,292
Break it...

971
01:19:11,520 --> 01:19:14,159
'Now do a headstand.'

972
01:19:14,444 --> 01:19:18,827
'A headstand. Slowly!'
- Headstand.

973
01:19:18,917 --> 01:19:21,873
Okay.
- Slowly, slowly...

974
01:19:24,583 --> 01:19:26,042
'Look at the omelette cooking.'

975
01:19:26,132 --> 01:19:27,459
Madam, can you see it?

976
01:19:27,792 --> 01:19:28,792
How is it?

977
01:19:31,177 --> 01:19:32,792
Great!

978
01:19:32,882 --> 01:19:37,417
It's good, right? After so much
hard work it has to be good!

979
01:19:38,109 --> 01:19:40,708
'Keep your legs down.'

980
01:19:41,131 --> 01:19:46,417
'Now slowly stand up.
Slowly.'

981
01:19:46,792 --> 01:19:49,244
'Be seated'
- Again!

982
01:19:49,334 --> 01:19:53,804
'and place your right leg

983
01:19:53,894 --> 01:19:55,570
on your neck.'

984
01:19:55,660 --> 01:19:57,467
Right leg.
- 'Slowly.'

985
01:19:57,666 --> 01:20:00,750
'Don't do it in a hurry.'

986
01:20:01,344 --> 01:20:05,334
'Place your right leg
on your neck.'

987
01:20:05,583 --> 01:20:07,000
Oh God!

988
01:20:07,125 --> 01:20:10,792
The spices used in the omelette
are wonderful. - What's happening?

989
01:20:11,249 --> 01:20:15,846
I'm stuck! I'm locked!

990
01:20:16,062 --> 01:20:19,792
Let me go!

991
01:20:21,311 --> 01:20:25,250
The keys!
No!

992
01:20:26,502 --> 01:20:31,107
Madam, please unlock me too.

993
01:20:32,232 --> 01:20:33,417
Please!

994
01:20:33,666 --> 01:20:36,000
Oh, God!

995
01:20:36,090 --> 01:20:41,792
Sir, your neck is trapped
with your legs. - Yes.

996
01:20:41,986 --> 01:20:44,792
What is your opinion on this?
- Very bad.

997
01:20:45,332 --> 01:20:46,397
Hey! Hey!

998
01:20:46,487 --> 01:20:48,167
Thank you.
- Okay.

999
01:20:48,257 --> 01:20:52,042
Please help me!
Help!

1000
01:20:52,568 --> 01:20:55,569
Help!
Help!

1001
01:20:56,301 --> 01:20:58,375
Allahrakha...

1002
01:20:59,263 --> 01:21:01,471
Don't try to run away!

1003
01:21:01,666 --> 01:21:05,243
Or Allahrakha
will gouge your eyes out!

1004
01:21:08,083 --> 01:21:12,875
Come here and help me
get rid of this situation.

1005
01:21:13,167 --> 01:21:15,000
Come!

1006
01:21:16,625 --> 01:21:18,417
My neck!

1007
01:21:19,417 --> 01:21:24,042
My body is aching!

1008
01:21:24,167 --> 01:21:26,501
'Your French omelette is ready.'

1009
01:21:27,133 --> 01:21:31,459
'Eat it and...'
- I'll show it! I'll hit it!

1010
01:21:32,958 --> 01:21:34,666
Hey girl!
Hold this!

1011
01:21:36,881 --> 01:21:41,074
I'm going to the railway station.

1012
01:21:41,250 --> 01:21:42,906
When I return,

1013
01:21:42,996 --> 01:21:47,224
keep the French omelette ready.

1014
01:21:47,314 --> 01:21:48,459
Understood?!

1015
01:21:49,667 --> 01:21:55,750
Keep a watch on her, Allahrakha.

1016
01:22:21,792 --> 01:22:23,250
Don't be afraid, dear.

1017
01:22:23,340 --> 01:22:26,958
Whenever the train passes,
the houses of the poor shake.

1018
01:22:27,499 --> 01:22:30,542
I'm returning
from a pilgrimage to Shirdi.

1019
01:22:31,040 --> 01:22:34,833
I heard that
Iqbal brought you here forcefully.

1020
01:22:35,750 --> 01:22:37,375
The donkey!

1021
01:22:37,792 --> 01:22:39,750
No decision
can be taken in a hurry.

1022
01:22:40,375 --> 01:22:42,375
You can go.

1023
01:22:42,666 --> 01:22:44,334
It...
- Shut up.

1024
01:23:00,118 --> 01:23:02,083
You have troubled me a lot.

1025
01:23:03,344 --> 01:23:05,334
I won't spare you.

1026
01:23:10,209 --> 01:23:12,292
You wanted
a French omelette, right?

1027
01:23:12,792 --> 01:23:15,417
Why are you killing
a dead person?

1028
01:23:17,792 --> 01:23:20,583
He wished to have
a French omelette made by you.

1029
01:23:21,209 --> 01:23:24,250
When he was
walking towards the station,

1030
01:23:25,042 --> 01:23:28,792
the train broke him
into little pieces.

1031
01:23:29,949 --> 01:23:33,666
Every piece
was yelling out your name.

1032
01:23:37,391 --> 01:23:39,941
'IQBAL COOLIE MEETS WITH AN ACCIDENT'
- Why did you leave us like this, Iqbal?

1033
01:23:40,250 --> 01:23:43,520
But there was no such news
in today's paper.

1034
01:23:43,797 --> 01:23:48,401
No one prints news
of a poor person like him.

1035
01:23:48,791 --> 01:23:53,603
If a person like your uncle had
