the needs of so many people!

1788
02:32:05,474 --> 02:32:06,764
You'll have to agree,

1789
02:32:07,094 --> 02:32:10,348
nothing can happen
without rich people.

1790
02:32:10,537 --> 02:32:11,930
How's that possible?

1791
02:32:12,936 --> 02:32:16,097
Have you ever heard of rich people
sacrificing their lives at war?

1792
02:32:16,813 --> 02:32:18,342
It's the poor man

1793
02:32:18,432 --> 02:32:21,180
who sacrifices his life
and makes his nation proud.

1794
02:32:24,096 --> 02:32:27,840
The world keeps moving
because of us.

1795
02:32:28,386 --> 02:32:30,828
Right from the Taj Mahal
to the smallest hut...

1796
02:32:30,990 --> 02:32:36,124
Every building has been
created by people like us.

1797
02:32:38,704 --> 02:32:43,767
The rich have created everything
by resorting to corruption.

1798
02:32:44,637 --> 02:32:46,264
These people buy votes for Rs 10...

1799
02:32:46,865 --> 02:32:48,889
Get approvals for Rs. 100...

1800
02:32:49,228 --> 02:32:51,722
Pay thousands to pass an exam...

1801
02:32:51,940 --> 02:32:54,389
Shell out millions
to get tenders passed.

1802
02:32:54,479 --> 02:32:59,656
Only if the corrupt fail
will the nation progress.

1803
02:33:01,993 --> 02:33:04,970
Stop him
or I'll get a heart attack!

1804
02:33:05,060 --> 02:33:06,430
Where is Zafar?
- Dad!

1805
02:33:06,597 --> 02:33:09,389
Do I have to answer that?
- No!

1806
02:33:11,139 --> 02:33:13,389
I'll answer this question.

1807
02:33:15,728 --> 02:33:16,930
Move!

1808
02:33:21,854 --> 02:33:22,972
Brothers...

1809
02:33:23,852 --> 02:33:26,264
This blood and injuries,

1810
02:33:26,918 --> 02:33:28,930
were caused by this porter!

1811
02:33:29,732 --> 02:33:32,014
He didn't want me to come here,

1812
02:33:32,462 --> 02:33:35,847
so he shot me
by sending his girlfriend.

1813
02:33:35,937 --> 02:33:37,076
Lies!

1814
02:33:37,166 --> 02:33:40,056
Then check who's arrested
at the police station!

1815
02:33:41,132 --> 02:33:46,330
But I'll shower flowers on the one
who tried to do this.

1816
02:33:53,426 --> 02:33:55,056
Don't look there.

1817
02:33:55,954 --> 02:33:57,847
Listen to me first
and then look over there.

1818
02:33:58,796 --> 02:34:02,748
Your father, Mr. Aslam is alive
and he's in my custody.

1819
02:34:04,172 --> 02:34:06,097
My father?
- Yes.

1820
02:34:06,902 --> 02:34:09,790
The person
who's coming to that platform.

1821
02:34:22,450 --> 02:34:24,847
Your father's life
is in danger right now.

1822
02:34:25,522 --> 02:34:28,936
So you better quit
the elections, or...

1823
02:34:35,530 --> 02:34:36,972
What's the matter, son?

1824
02:34:39,430 --> 02:34:40,354
Uncle.

1825
02:34:41,775 --> 02:34:45,212
Is the person standing there,
my dad?

1826
02:34:53,560 --> 02:34:56,805
Aslam!
Yes, he is your dad!

1827
02:35:02,061 --> 02:35:04,972
Welcome, Mr. Zafar.

1828
02:35:06,472 --> 02:35:12,156
Zafar has done great work
while offering a garland to me,

1829
02:35:13,521 --> 02:35:17,082
that I can't say anything,
nor defeat him.

1830
02:35:18,448 --> 02:35:19,513
My...

1831
02:35:21,006 --> 02:35:25,513
The answer to my prayers
is with him.

1832
02:35:27,312 --> 02:35:32,956
I withdraw my name
from the election

1833
02:35:34,389 --> 02:35:35,709
and apologize to all.

1834
02:35:35,799 --> 02:35:37,639
No...

1835
02:35:55,293 --> 02:36:00,264
He hasn't decided to step down

1836
02:36:00,555 --> 02:36:03,222
because of good work by Zafar.

1837
02:36:03,312 --> 02:36:06,907
Zafar must have blackmailed him!

1838
02:36:06,997 --> 02:36:11,430
This woman will voice out
all his bad deeds.

1839
02:36:24,204 --> 02:36:25,472
My husband,

1840
02:36:26,214 --> 02:36:27,472
Iqbal's father,

1841
02:36:28,356 --> 02:36:29,847
greetings to you!

1842
02:36:30,617 --> 02:36:32,597
Greetings to you, dear!

1843
02:36:32,756 --> 02:36:35,306
My brothers...
- How did she speak?

1844
02:36:36,695 --> 02:36:39,513
Mom, don't say anything
against Zafar.

1845
02:36:39,717 --> 02:36:40,972
Father's life is in danger.

1846
02:36:42,200 --> 02:36:46,143
The Almighty who united
both of us,

1847
02:36:46,885 --> 02:36:48,889
will save his life.

1848
02:36:52,353 --> 02:36:56,597
Mr Zafar, you must be
very surprised to hear my voice.

1849
02:36:57,258 --> 02:37:03,011
It's God's miracle that
he returned my memory and speech.

1850
02:37:03,319 --> 02:37:05,197
Cut the wire of the microphone.

1851
02:37:05,287 --> 02:37:10,855
My brothers, this person who's
trying to collect your sympathies,

1852
02:37:10,945 --> 02:37:13,207
is a rascal and a cheat!

1853
02:37:13,297 --> 02:37:14,779
He has destroyed many...

1854
02:37:20,502 --> 02:37:24,942
You can't stop me
by cutting an electric wire.

1855
02:37:25,032 --> 02:37:29,226
I'll make sure that my voice
reaches every soul.

1856
02:37:29,389 --> 02:37:32,139
He killed my father!

1857
02:37:33,590 --> 02:37:37,930
He kept giving me electric shocks
for 20 long years,

1858
02:37:38,020 --> 02:37:41,882
so that I don't recall
my husband and son.

1859
02:37:41,972 --> 02:37:44,975
This is injustice!

1860
02:37:45,065 --> 02:37:47,805
My brothers, I used to give her
electric shocks,

1861
02:37:47,895 --> 02:37:51,680
at the advice of a doctor
and not at my own will,

1862
02:37:52,176 --> 02:37:54,014
as she was mentally ill.

1863
02:37:54,306 --> 02:37:56,847
You can ask him if you want!

1864
02:37:58,359 --> 02:38:00,472
My dear brothers,
what shall I say?

1865
02:38:00,951 --> 02:38:04,597
Mr Zafar has spent his life
looking for her husband.

1866
02:38:04,989 --> 02:38:09,181
When he found him alive,
he brought him here,

1867
02:38:09,657 --> 02:38:15,097
so that he could unite them
in front of everyone!

1868
02:38:16,320 --> 02:38:21,014
If you curse him, it'll be
as good as cursing humanity.

1869
02:38:22,097 --> 02:38:25,680
Mr. Aslam, proceed.
Your wife is waiting for you.

1870
02:38:32,358 --> 02:38:33,455
What are you doing?

1871
02:38:33,887 --> 02:38:35,680
I'm doing the right thing.

1872
02:38:35,770 --> 02:38:38,306
We could lose a lot
if we don't do this.

1873
02:38:38,555 --> 02:38:42,139
If the public gets violent,
we'll be done for.

1874
02:38:42,229 --> 02:38:45,597
I don't care about the public,
money and an election.

1875
02:38:46,406 --> 02:38:48,014
I've never learnt to accept defeat.

1876
02:38:48,795 --> 02:38:52,306
If I don't get Salma,
she can never be with anyone else!

1877
02:39:03,863 --> 02:39:07,385
Let's go! I think
something will go wrong here!

1878
02:39:14,597 --> 02:39:16,138
Uncle!
- Father!

1879
02:39:17,616 --> 02:39:18,805
Uncle!
- Father!

1880
02:39:22,430 --> 02:39:23,847
I'll go on.

1881
02:39:24,714 --> 02:39:25,930
I've received the signal.

1882
02:39:28,008 --> 02:39:29,348
Iqbal...

1883
02:39:30,745 --> 02:39:33,174
He...
- Father!

1884
02:40:21,661 --> 02:40:23,715
We have to break the stage!

1885
02:40:34,333 --> 02:40:35,593
Move back!

1886
02:40:39,700 --> 02:40:42,297
Sunny!

1887
02:40:46,356 --> 02:40:48,738
Don't block my way,
or I'll kill everybody!

1888
02:40:50,744 --> 02:40:53,237
Leave me!
Let me go!

1889
02:42:17,967 --> 02:42:19,851
Come on.
- Leave me!

1890
02:42:20,310 --> 02:42:21,351
Zafar!

1891
02:42:22,523 --> 02:42:27,332
It's a holy shrine
and you can't enter it.

1892
02:42:27,422 --> 02:42:29,836
No one can stop Zafar!
- No!

1893
02:42:32,561 --> 02:42:34,534
Let go of me!

1894
02:42:36,041 --> 02:42:37,819
Leave my hand!

1895
02:42:40,480 --> 02:42:43,234
God.
- Come on!

1896
02:42:49,194 --> 02:42:50,701
Oh, Lord! Please perform a miracle!

1897
02:43:03,400 --> 02:43:04,442
How long will you survive?

1898
02:43:05,102 --> 02:43:07,150
There are three bullets left!

1899
02:43:07,442 --> 02:43:08,682
Shoot me!

1900
02:43:09,852 --> 02:43:13,914
If you have the weapons to kill
I have God with me!

1901
02:43:15,108 --> 02:43:20,613
Let's see if this sheet saves me
or becomes my shroud.

1902
02:43:21,484 --> 02:43:22,502
Shoot me!

1903
02:43:26,853 --> 02:43:32,830
'Nothing except Allah is worthy
of worship!'

1904
02:43:41,234 --> 02:43:49,812
'Peace and blessings be upon, Mohammad,
the messenger of God.'

1905
02:44:20,790 --> 02:44:28,730
'Nothing except Allah is worthy
of worship!'

1906
02:45:21,590 --> 02:45:26,564
"Allah is great."

1907
02:45:27,694 --> 02:45:29,053
Iqbal!
My son!

1908
02:45:29,475 --> 02:45:31,502
My, son!

1909
02:45:31,998 --> 02:45:35,549
My son.
- Enough, enough mother!

1910
02:45:36,909 --> 02:45:40,841
Mom, I'm alive
just to listen to this word.

1911
02:45:42,084 --> 02:45:47,444
Please call me your son once more.

1912
02:45:48,378 --> 02:45:52,068
I'm embracing you after so long.

1913
02:45:52,619 --> 02:45:56,979
Don't leave me.
Don't leave me, my son.

1914
02:45:57,304 --> 02:45:58,734
No!

1915
02:45:59,089 --> 02:46:02,393
It's God...

1916
02:46:03,350 --> 02:46:06,782
who gives life or death.

1917
02:46:23,912 --> 02:46:25,133
Oh God.

1918
02:46:35,541 --> 02:46:36,713
'OPERATION THEATRE'

1919
02:47:13,062 --> 02:47:14,108
'OPERATION THEATRE'

1920
02:47:23,432 --> 02:47:26,395
Congratulations!
He is safe now.

1921
02:47:29,522 --> 02:47:30,762
Thank God!

1922
02:47:30,852 --> 02:47:33,043
God!
- Thank you!

1923
02:47:34,777 --> 02:47:36,803
Iqbal is here!

1924
02:47:36,893 --> 02:47:38,368
'St. PHILOMENA'S HOSPITAL'

1925
02:47:38,700 --> 02:47:44,349
Three cheers for Iqbal!
- Praise Iqbal!

1926
02:47:44,439 --> 02:47:46,282
Three cheers to you!

1927
02:47:47,112 --> 02:47:48,610
I had died.

1928
02:47:49,276 --> 02:47:52,989
I'm back
only because of your prayers.

1929
